<title>NETHERLANDS: Krasnapolsky to build hotel in Israel.</title>
<headline>Krasnapolsky to build hotel in Israel.</headline>
<dateline>AMSTERDAM 1997-05-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Dutch hotel and restaurant chain Krasnapolsky NV said on Monday it had signed a letter of intent with Israeli ALevy Investment &amp; Construction Ltd to form a venture to build a 311-room hotel in Israel.</p>
<p>Total investment will amount to $50,000,000.</p>
<p>The Israeli government will provide a subsidy of at least $10,000,000, Krasnapolsky said.</p>
<p>Krasnapolsky will hold a 50 percent stake in the joint venture and will contribute up to $7,500,000 to the venture.</p>
<p>Krasnapolsky said it expected the hotel to open in 1999.</p>
